  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-04 synthetic)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. Model Risk Level 3. Thirteen credibility factors are addressed; twelve are formally assessed. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — is recorded as not-assessed on the grounds that the assessors judged it inapplicable to the COU (the pump geometry is identical between simulation and bench test, so no input-parameter mapping is required). However, the correct encoding for that judgment would be factorStatus 'not-applicable'; the package instead carries factorStatus 'not-assessed', leaving a material epistemic gap at MRL 3. This is the targeted W-EP-04 weakness.",
